---
# Clang-tidy configuration for kernel (device) code.
#
# Strategy (mirrors the host .clang-tidy):
#   Enable ALL checks with *, then opt-out of checks that currently fire.
#   To enable a check: remove its -check-name line below, fix violations,
#   and send a PR.
#
# === Why so many exclusions? ===
#
# Kernel code is cross-compiled for Tenstorrent RISC-V cores. For clang-tidy
# we re-parse it with host clang using stub defines, which means:
#   - Firmware headers trigger many style/modernize checks (not our code)
#   - Inline asm in firmware headers triggers hicpp-no-assembler (242K hits)
#   - Device code intentionally uses C-style patterns (reinterpret_cast,
#     pointer arithmetic) for hardware register access
#   - Compile-time arguments are provided as dummy values during analysis

Checks: >
